## 4. Orchestration Entrypoint

**File:** `Chucks_List_Builder.py`

**Responsibilities:**
- Parse all CLI flags (see Section 11)
- Emit `[REMIND]` warnings for any per-issue customization the operator
  has not set (callout text, bottom callout text)
- Run each pipeline stage as a subprocess, in order
- Capture stdout and stderr from each stage and route to the run log
- Surface `[WARN]`, `[ERROR]`, and `[REMIND]` lines from subprocesses
- Halt immediately on any non-zero subprocess exit — do not proceed to compile
  after a failed preprocess
- Emit a final build summary listing every stage and its result
- Forward `--callout` and `--bottom-callout` flags to compile stages only
  (not to preprocess stages)
- Never forward flags that a subprocess does not accept

**Stage execution order:**

```
If --issue-type includes bulletins:
  1. preprocess_bulletin_text.py --issue-date <date>
  2. compile_bulletin.py --issue-date <date> [--callout ...] [--bottom-callout ...]

If --issue-type includes events:
  3. preprocess_events_text.py --issue-date <date>
  4. compile_events.py --issue-date <date> [--callout ...] [--bottom-callout ...]
```

**Callout reminders:** If `--callout` was not passed, the builder must emit:

```
[REMIND] No --callout set. Using default bulletin top callout.
         Edit in Builder or pass: --callout "Your text here"
```

The default callout text must be shown (first 70 characters) so the operator
can confirm whether the default is acceptable for this issue.

