Typography is set for the primary audience: elderly readers who may be
using default browser zoom. These values must not be reduced. If a design
change requires smaller text, it is not an acceptable change.

### 7.3 Layout Structure

```
<body>
  [outer wrapper table — full width, page background color]
    [inner content table — max-width 680px, centered]
      [header row — logo/title bar]
      [callout row — top callout box]
      [TOC row — "In this Bulletin" / "In this Events Edition"]
      [section rows — repeated per section]
        [section heading bar]
        [entry rows — repeated per item]
          [entry title]
          [entry meta — dates, location, contact]
          [entry body]
          [entry image block — if present]
      [callout row — bottom callout box]
      [footer row]
```

Maximum content width: **680px**. This is the standard safe width for email
clients including Outlook. Content must not overflow this width.

### 7.4 Dark Mode

Both email outputs include a `<style>` block with `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`
overrides. Dark mode must override:

- Page background → `#1a1008`
- Content background → `#2a1f10`
- Body text → `#e8d8c0`
- Links → `#c8a878`
- Section heading background → `#8b6b4a`
- Entry backgrounds → appropriately darkened earth tones

Dark mode is not optional. It was included in the approved design.

