## 8. Accessibility Requirements

Chuck's List serves a community that includes elderly readers, low-vision
readers, and readers on aging devices. These requirements are non-negotiable.
They are constraints, not suggestions.

### Text Size and Spacing

- **Body font size: 20px minimum.** Do not reduce this.
- **Line height: 1.75 minimum.** Tight leading is hard for elderly readers.
- **Paragraph spacing:** Visible gap between paragraphs. `margin-bottom: 1em` minimum.
- **Heading hierarchy:** Entry titles > Section headings > TOC labels.
  Never skip levels.

### Contrast

- Body text (`#2c1f0e`) on entry background (`#faf6ef`): passes WCAG AA.
- Do not introduce text-on-background combinations that have not been
  contrast-checked.
- Muted or light gray body text is not acceptable at any size.

### Links

- Every link must have a human-readable label. Raw URLs as visible link
  text are prohibited — they are unreadable when read aloud by screen
  readers and untrackable by Zoho.
- `mailto:` links must use a human name or readable email as the label —
  not the raw address.
- Links must be visually distinguishable from body text (color + underline
  or color alone if contrast is sufficient).

### Images

- Every `<img>` must have an `alt` attribute.
- Decorative images: `alt=""`.
- Content images: descriptive text matching the post title and image number.
- Images must never be the sole carrier of important information.
  Text must always accompany image content.

### Email Client Safety

- No JavaScript. Email clients strip it.
- No CSS `position: fixed` or `position: absolute`. Email clients ignore or
  break these.
- No CSS grid or flexbox in the email body. Use table-based layout.
- Inline styles on all elements that need consistent rendering across clients.
  `<style>` blocks are supported in modern clients but may be stripped in
  older ones — critical layout and color must be inline.

