## 10. Source Data Contract

### 10.1 Bulletins CSV

Export from `Chucks-list-MASTER.ods` Bulletins sheet.

| Column | Required | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Received` | Yes | Date | Date item was submitted |
| `Expires` | Yes | Date | Last issue date to include this item |
| `Section` | Yes | Text | Must match canonical name or alias |
| `Title` | Yes | Text | Plain text, no Markdown |
| `Body` | Yes | Text | Plain text with optional Markdown |
| `Image` | No | Text | Pipe-separated filename(s) in `Images/` |
| `notes` | No | Text | Internal only — never rendered |

**Canonical section names and accepted aliases:**

| Canonical | Accepted aliases |
|---|---|
| Urgent Bulletins | Urgent, URGENT |
| Housing Opportunities | Housing, Homes |
| Swap Market | Swap, For Sale, Trade |
| Local Services & Help | Services, Help, Local Services |
| Community Announcements | Announcements, Community |

### 10.2 Events CSV

Export from `Chucks-list-MASTER.ods` Events sheet.

| Column | Required | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Received` | No | Date | Not used for filtering |
| `Starts` | Yes | Date | First issue date to include |
| `Expires` | Yes | Date | Last issue date to include (→ `Ends`) |
| `Section` | No | Text | Used for grouping |
| `Title` | Yes | Text | Plain text |
| `Text` | Yes | Text | Plain text with optional Markdown |
| `Image` | No | Text | Pipe-separated filename(s) in `Images/` |
| `notes` | No | Text | Internal only — never rendered |

### 10.3 Multi-Image Fields

The `Image` column accepts 1–3 pipe-separated filenames:

```
Images/photo.jpg
Images/photo1.jpg|Images/photo2.jpg
Images/photo1.jpg|Images/photo2.jpg|Images/photo3.jpg
```

Rules:
- Each part is trimmed of whitespace before use.
- Entries beyond index 2 (4th image and beyond) are dropped with a `[WARN]`.
  The operator is instructed to move extras to cloud storage and share a
  link in the body text.
- Each image renders as its own `<img>` and `<a>` pair.
- Posts with 4 or more images should use cloud storage (e.g., Google Drive,
  a public album) and include a link in the body text instead.

### 10.4 Markdown in Body Text

Staff are not required to use Markdown. The system handles plain text
naturally. For staff who do use it:

| Input | Output |
|---|---|
| Blank line | New paragraph |
| `## Heading` | Subheading (`<h3>`) |
| `- item`, `* item`, `• item` | Bulleted list |
| `[Label](https://url)` | Hyperlink |
| `[Label](mailto:email)` | Email link |

**Prohibited patterns (will trigger `[ERROR]` in bulletins pipeline):**
- `[https://example.com](https://example.com)` — label is a raw URL
- `[email@example.com](mailto:email@example.com)` — label is a raw email

**Auto-fixed patterns (bulletins pipeline, logged as `[WARN]`):**
- Bare `email@example.com` → `[email@example.com](mailto:email@example.com)`
- Bare `www.example.com` → `[www.example.com](https://www.example.com)`

