## 11. CLI Specification

All flags must be explicitly defined in `argparse`. No flag may be implied,
guessed from environment variables, or silently ignored.

| Flag | Type | Default | Passed to |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--issue-date` | `str` (YYYY-MM-DD) | **required** | All stages |
| `--issue-type` | `bulletin\|events\|both` | `both` | Entrypoint only (controls which pipelines run) |
| `--callout` | `str` | None | Compile stages only |
| `--bottom-callout` | `str` | None | Compile stages only |
| `--debug` | `store_true` | False | Entrypoint + subprocesses via log level |
| `--log-to-file` | `store_true` | False | Entrypoint |
| `--no-open-vscode` | `store_true` | False | Entrypoint |

`--debug` must be defined as:
```python
parser.add_argument("--debug", action="store_true", help="Enable debug logging")
```

It must never be assumed to exist without this declaration. A missing flag
definition crashes any subprocess call that passes it through.

