## 12. Logging and Operator Guidance

### Message Levels

| Prefix | Meaning | Color (if terminal supports) |
|---|---|---|
| `[OK]` | Stage completed successfully | Green |
| `[INFO]` | Informational — no action needed | Default |
| `[REMIND]` | Per-issue customization point — review before sending | Yellow |
| `[WARN]` | Row skipped — fix in source data | Yellow |
| `[ERROR]` | Pipeline blocked — must fix before output is usable | Red |

### Required Content of Every WARN and ERROR

```
[WARN] Row {N}: '{field}' value '{value}' — {description of problem}.
       Fix: {exact action} in Chucks-list-MASTER.ods row {N}.
```

Never emit a bare Python exception as operator output. Catch all expected
failure modes and translate them into actionable messages.

### Build Summary

The entrypoint must emit a build summary at the end of every run:

```
══════════════════════════════════════════
  Chuck's List Build Summary — 2026-06-07
══════════════════════════════════════════
  [OK]    Bulletins preprocess — 12 items, 2 skipped
  [OK]    Bulletins compile — chucks_bulletin_final_output.html
  [OK]    Events preprocess — 8 items, 0 skipped
  [OK]    Events compile — chucks_events_final_output.html
══════════════════════════════════════════
  Build complete. Review any [WARN] lines before uploading to Zoho.
══════════════════════════════════════════
```

If any stage failed, the summary must state clearly:

```
  ⚠ BUILD INCOMPLETE — do not upload partial output to Zoho Campaigns.
```

