## 15. What Must Never Change

These decisions are made. Any proposal to change them requires explicit
operator approval, not just engineering convenience.

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Two separate pipelines | Different data shapes, different logic, different audiences |
| Preprocess before compile, never merged | Separation of concerns; each stage testable independently |
| QUOTE_ALL on all DictWriters | Protects multi-line and Markdown-syntax cells |
| Escape before linkify | Prevents `<a>` tags from being HTML-escaped |
| Mesa Verde color palette | Visual identity for Montezuma County — approved and final |
| 20px body text, 1.75 line-height | Accessibility for elderly readers — non-negotiable |
| Table-based email layout | Email client compatibility — CSS layout is not safe in email |
| One command to build | Operator simplicity — complexity hides in the pipeline, not the interface |
| Zoho Campaigns for delivery | Out of scope for the builder — do not build send capability |
| No database | Current phase only — migration is in the roadmap, not in this codebase |
| `Path(__file__).resolve().parent` | Reliable path resolution regardless of terminal CWD |
| Forward-slash URL paths in HTML | Windows backslash paths are invalid in HTML src/href |

