## Appendix A — Confirmed Bug History

These bugs have been confirmed and fixed in this codebase. Do not reintroduce them.

| ID | Description | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| BUG-1 | Callouts never prompted | Builder ran compilers with no `--callout` arg; operator had no signal | `emit_callout_reminders()` added; flags wired through entrypoint |
| BUG-2 | Markdown links rendered as raw text in events email | Missing `QUOTE_ALL` on `events/preprocess_events_text.py` DictWriter; `[]()` cells written unquoted | `quoting=csv.QUOTE_ALL` added |
| BUG-3 | "here" link in Shamanism retreat post not rendering | Same root cause as BUG-2 | Fixed by BUG-2 fix |
| BUG-4 | All bulletins skipped; zero-item output exits 0 | `parse_date()` had no `M/D/YYYY` handler; LibreOffice exports dates in that format; all rows hit fallthrough warn | `DATE_RE_LONG` added at module level; `long_match` block inserted in `parse_date()` |
| BUG-5 | Windows backslash paths in HTML `src`/`href` | Raw `pathlib.Path` strings used in HTML attributes produce `\` on Windows; `src` and `href` sometimes referenced different paths | `to_web_path()` helper using `Path.as_posix()` + `urllib.parse.quote` |
| BUG-6 | Pipe-delimited image field not split before render | `build_image_html()` injected the whole `"img1.png \| img2.png"` string into one `src=` and one `href=` | Split on `\|`, render one `<img>`/`<a>` pair per filename; `MAX_INLINE_IMAGES = 3` |
| BUG-7 | False-positive Markdown validation on parentheses in URLs | Naive raw paren-counter across full Body field fired on valid CommonMark links with `(` in URL targets | Validate at `[label](target)` segment level only; not yet fully implemented |
| BUG-8 | `--debug` flag not defined in argparse | Flag used in workflow without `parser.add_argument("--debug", ...)` declaration | Added explicitly with `action="store_true"` |

